    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-02-06T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-02-06T17:00:00-05:00" n="455"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d455">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">660M116/3a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Lithuania</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="2" xml:id="d455fn2">The Minister was accredited to Estonia,
                        Latvia, and Lithuania, with residence at Riga.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-02-06T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 6, 1935—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5. Please submit as soon as possible by mail comprehensive report on the present
                    treatment by Lithuania of American trade. Legation at Riga has been requested to
                    forward you a copy of a report from Tallinn<note n="3" xml:id="d455fn3">Despatch
                        No. 43, October 6, 1934, <ref target="frus1934v02#pg_130">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1934, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 130</ref>.</note> to serve in form and
                    content as a model. Special efforts should be made to obtain comparable
                    information from Lithuanian officials and importers. Your report should show
                    definitely whether American trade is at the present time receiving
                    most-favored-nation treatment in Lithuania and, if not, precisely wherein such
                    treatment is being denied.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
